          <actionDate>2016-09-22</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill establishes a U.S. Green Bank that provides financial support to assist regional, state, and local institutions finance: (1) clean energy (e.g. solar or wind energy) projects, or (2) energy efficiency projects that reduce energy use or substantially reduce greenhouse gas emissions. </p> <p>The Department of the Treasury must issue Green Bonds to provide the bank with: (1) an initial capitalization of $10 billion; and (2) additional capitalization, upon the bank's request, of no more than $50 billion in aggregate at any one time.</p> <p>Treasury must also establish a revolving Green Bank Establishment Fund.</p>]]></text>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
